{"content":"---\ntitle: \"How to: Span Rows and Columns in a TableLayoutPanel Control\"\nms.date: \"03/30/2017\"\nf1_keywords: \n  - \"net.ComponentModel.StyleCollectionEditor.TLP.SpanRowsColumns\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"columns [Windows Forms], spanning\"\n  - \"merging cells\"\n  - \"TableLayoutPanel control [Windows Forms], spanning rows and columns\"\n  - \"rows [Windows Forms], spanning\"\n  - \"cells [Windows Forms], merging\"\nms.assetid: a8a2fdd3-a848-48b0-a4cd-4e85ebded87e\n---\n# How to: Span Rows and Columns in a TableLayoutPanel Control\nControls in a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TableLayoutPanel> control can span adjacent rows and columns.  \n  \n> [!NOTE]\n>  The dialog boxes and menu commands you see might differ from those described in Help depending on your active settings or edition. To change your settings, choose **Import and Export Settings** on the **Tools** menu. For more information, see [Personalize the Visual Studio IDE](/visualstudio/ide/personalizing-the-visual-studio-ide).  \n  \n### To span columns and rows  \n  \n1.  Drag a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TableLayoutPanel> control from the **Toolbox** onto your form.  \n  \n2.  Drag a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Button> control from the **Toolbox** into the upper-left cell of the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TableLayoutPanel> control.  \n  \n3.  Set the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Button> control's **ColumnSpan** property to **2**. Note that the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Button> control spans the first and second columns.  \n  \n4.  Set the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Button> control's **RowSpan** property to **2**. Note that the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Button> control spans the first and second rows.  \n  \n5.  Set the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Button> control's **ColumnSpan** property to **1**. Note that the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Button> control moves into the first column and spans the first and second rows.  \n  \n## See also\n\n- [TableLayoutPanel Control](tablelayoutpanel-control-windows-forms.md)\n","nodes":[{"pos":[4,454],"embed":true,"restype":"x-metadata","content":"title: \"How to: Span Rows and Columns in a TableLayoutPanel Control\"\nms.date: \"03/30/2017\"\nf1_keywords: \n  - \"net.ComponentModel.StyleCollectionEditor.TLP.SpanRowsColumns\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"columns [Windows Forms], spanning\"\n  - \"merging cells\"\n  - \"TableLayoutPanel control [Windows Forms], spanning rows and columns\"\n  - \"rows [Windows Forms], spanning\"\n  - \"cells [Windows Forms], merging\"\nms.assetid: a8a2fdd3-a848-48b0-a4cd-4e85ebded87e","nodes":[{"content":"How to: Span Rows and Columns in a TableLayoutPanel Control","nodes":[{"pos":[0,59],"content":"How to: Span Rows and Columns in a TableLayoutPanel Control","nodes":[{"content":"How to: Span Rows and Columns in a TableLayoutPanel Control","pos":[0,59]}]}],"path":["title"],"nosxs":false}],"yml":true},{"pos":[461,520],"content":"How to: Span Rows and Columns in a TableLayoutPanel Control","linkify":"How to: Span Rows and Columns in a TableLayoutPanel Control","nodes":[{"content":"How to: Span Rows and Columns in a TableLayoutPanel Control","pos":[0,59]}]},{"pos":[521,623],"content":"Controls in a <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Forms.TableLayoutPanel&gt;</ph> control can span adjacent rows and columns.","source":"Controls in a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.TableLayoutPanel> control can span adjacent rows and columns."},{"pos":[631,976],"content":"[!NOTE]\n The dialog boxes and menu commands you see might differ from those described in Help depending on your active settings or edition. To change your settings, choose **Import and Export Settings** on the **Tools** menu. For more information, see [Personalize the Visual Studio IDE](/visualstudio/ide/personalizing-the-visual-studio-ide).","leadings":["","> "],"nodes":[{"content":"The dialog boxes and menu commands you see might differ from those described in Help depending on your active settings or edition. To change your settings,